verbose_text: Transfusion of KEL RBCs into C5 KO and FcgammaR KO mice failed to result in altered levels of anti-KEL IgM or IgG when compared to B6 mice, suggesting that while C3 plays an inhibitory role in the Ab response to KEL, C5 and FcgammaRs do not appear to negatively or positively impact antigen levels or anti-KEL Ab formation following KEL RBC transfusion.
